        "unit": "W",
        "description": "Typical range for industrial laser cleaning of delicate materials like plaster to avoid thermal damage; starting at 100 W for light contamination removal. Max safe below 500 W to prevent substrate cracking due to plaster's low thermal conductivity (~0.5 W/m·K). Source: Manufacturer specs from IPG Photonics YLR series and studies on laser cleaning of gypsum-based plasters (e.g., J. Cult. Herit. 2018)."
